namespace NexusForever.Script.Instance.Dungeon.RuinsOfKelVoreth
{
    public enum CommunicatorMessage
    {
        ToricAntevian1   = 3941, // Right. There's the only way in - The Blood Pit. That's where the Osun indulge in their barbarous bloodsports. All you've got to do is survive. Easy isn't it?
        AvraDarkos1      = 3953, // Gaze upon the grandeur of Kel Voreth, $(player.class). Our agents report the Osun of Auroria have reclaimed this fortress in order to recover the secrets of ancient Osun technology. The Black Hoods cannot allow this, for the Osun seek only to bring war upon Nexus.
        ToricAntevian2   = 3942, // That was quite a show! Glad you didn't end up in the beast's belly. Are you ready to venture forth into the fortress? That's the spirit! May the Scions guide your path.
        AvraDarkos2      = 3954, // This is where those brutes hold their barbarous blood sports. All you have to do here is survive... if you can.
        ToricAntevian3   = 3943, // What's this? Looks like the Osun have unearthed an exo-lab full of ancient Eldan technology. We're not about to let them keep it, now are we?
        AvraDarkos3      = 3955, // So much for Grond. Another brute battered and beaten. Are you now prepared to journey further into the fortress?
        ToricAntevian4   = 3944, // The Osun have activated the exo-lab's defense systems. If you can find a way to turn off those phase blasters, getting through this mess should be a whole lot easier.
        AvraDarkos4      = 3956, // They've revealed the ruins of an excavated exo-lab. So many delicious Eldan secrets. We can't let the Osun to have that kind of power can we? Certainly not.
        ToricAntevian5   = 3946, // By the Scions, look at that mechanical monstrosity! Somehow it's controlling Eldan constructs - probably using something the Osun unearthed below. In the name of Dominus, destroy that machine!
        AvraDarkos5      = 3957, // Rotted ruin! Defense systems. You'll be safer if you can shut down the lab's phase blasters. Or feel free to be vaporized. The choice is up to you.
        ToricAntevian6   = 3947, // You fought like Azrion himself! Now comes the hard part. The Osun have rediscovered how to forge exanite - and exanite weapons are bad news for us. We have to stop them. Right? Right.
        AvraDarkos6      = 3958, // What's this? A war construct has enslaved its beastly mechanical brethren. I don't care how it was done, destroy him!
        ToricAntevian7   = 3948, // Light of the Luminai! It's hard to believe that the ancestors of these Osun savages actually built this fortress. How very far they've fallen, and how important they never gain such power again.
        AvraDarkos7      = 3959, // You have done well, but you're not done. The Osun have rediscovered how to forge exanite. And exanite weapons will make them invincible. You must stop them. Am I making myself clear?
        ToricAntevian8   = 3949, // These Osun are strong. Too strong... and once they start forging exanite weapons, they'll be unstoppable. We have to destroy their forges! Can't imagine they'll be too happy about it.
        AvraDarkos8      = 3960, // I can barely believe the Osun were once capable of such complex and colossal craftsmanship. We mustn't let them regain their bygone glory.
        ToricAntevian9   = 3950, // Watch yourself. Battlesworn warriors and Darkwitches ahead. Best to strike them down here than to let them wreak havoc outside the fortress walls. Up for another bout?
        AvraDarkos9      = 3961, // The Osun are formidable, but exanite weapons will make them truly frightening. Their forges must be destroyed and you must be the one to do it. And if you fail, you will have to face me instead.
        ToricAntevian10  = 3951, // There he is. The forgemaster. He's the one running the show. A real hard case, if I've ever seen one. Tristan's courage, friend. Are you ready to take him down?
        AvraDarkos10     = 3962, // And now, a complication. A minor melee with meddlesome monsters. Battlesworn and Darkwitches. Wound them and you'll weaken the Osun offensive.
        ToricAntevian11  = 3952, // Well done! We've still got a war in Auroria, but this will turn the tide. Go in the light of Dominus, friend. And the Radiant Legion gives you its thanks.
        AvraDarkos11     = 3963, // My spies were quite correct. The forgemaster is crafting exanite armaments. That's why you're here. Obliterate him.
        AvraDarkos12     = 3964  // So ends the Osun threat in Auroria. They won't rest until they've regained their glory - but never fear, the Widow's web is everywhere.
    }
}
